rack and field)|Central American Junior]]\n[[Category:2006 in Guatemalan sport|Central American Junior]]\n[[Category:2006 in Central American sport]]\n[[Category:International athletics competitions hosted by Guatemala]]\n[[Category:2006 in youth sport]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox Athletics Championships\n|Name = XIX Central American Junior and XIV Central American Youth Championships in Athletics\n|Logo =  \n|Size =  200px\n|Colour = \n|Optional caption = \n|Host city = [[Guatemala City|Ciudad de Guatemala]], [[Guatemala]] {{flagicon|Guatemala}}\n|Dates = May 11\u201313\n|Stadium = [[Estadio Cementos Progreso]]\n|Nations participating = 7\n|Athletes participating =  \n|Events = 80 (41 boys, 39 girls)\n|Records set = 17\n|Level = Junior and Youth\n|Previous = [[2005 Central American Junior and Youth Championships in Athletics|2005 Managua]]\n|Next = [[2007 Central American Junior and Youth Championships in Athletics|2007 San Salvador]]\n}}\n\nThe '''2006 [[Central American Junior and Youth Championships in Athletics]]''' were held at the [[Estadio Cementos Progreso]] in [[Guatemala City|Ciudad de Guatemala]], [[Guatemala]], between May 11\u201313, 2006.  Organized by the [[CADICA|Central American Isthmus Athletic Confederation]] (CADICA), it was the 19th edition of the Junior (U-20) and the 14th edition of the Youth (U-18) competition.  A total of 80 events were contested, 41 by boys and 39 by girls.  Overall winner on points was {{GUA}}.<ref name=diario_01>\n{{ Citation \n| last = Romero\n| first = Tom\u00e1s\n| date = May 16, 2006\n| title = El Salvador fue tercero en C.A. - Atletismo S\u00f3lo ganaron la categor\u00eda B del campeonato juvenil del istmo\n| url = http://www.elsalvador.com/noticias/2006/05/16/deportes/dep9.asp\n| page = \n| publisher = [[El Diario de Hoy]], San Salvador, El Salvador\n| language = Spanish\n| accessdate = February 23, 2013\n}}\n</ref>\n\n==Medal summary==\nComplete results can be found on the CADICA webpage.<ref name=cadica_01>\n{{ Citation \n| last = \n| first = \n| date = \n| title = XIX Campeonato Centroamericano Juvenil \"A\" - 11/05/2006 to 13/05/2006 - XIV Campeonato Centroamericano Juvenil \"B\" - Estadio Cementos Progreso - Resultados\n| url = http://www.atletismocadica.org/attachments/category/18/CA%20Juvenil%20A%20y%20B%202006%20GUA.pdf\n| page = \n| publisher = [[CADICA]]\n| language = Spanish\n| accessdate = February 23, 2013\n}}\n</ref>  Records were compiled from the results of the [[2007 Central American Junior and Youth Championships in Athletics|2007 championships]].<ref name=cadica_02>\n{{ Citation \n| last = \n| first = \n| date = \n| title = CAMPEONATO CENTROAMERICANO JUVENIL A Y B - SAN SALVADOR, EL SALVADOR - 25 - 27 DE MAYO DE 2007\n| url = http://www.atletismocadica.org/attachments/category/18/CA%20Juvenil%20A%20y%20B%202007%20ESA.pdf\n| page = \n| publisher = [[CADICA]]\n| language = Spanish\n| accessdate = February 23, 2013\n}}\n</ref>\n\n===Junior men===\n{| {{MedalistTable|type=Event|columns=2|fontsize=95}}\n|-\n|[[100 metres]] <small>(wind: -0.7&nbsp;m/s)</small>\n|{{flagathlete|[[Rolando Palacios]]|HON}} || 10.68\n|{{flagathlete|[[Alonso Edward]]|PAN}} || 11.05\n|{{flagathlete|[[Edwin Baltazar]]|GUA}} || 11.20\n|-\n|[[200 metres]] <small>(wind: +0.7&nbsp;m/s)</small>\n|{{flagathlete|[[Rolando Palacios]]|HON}} || 21.41 '''[[List of Central American Junior and Youth Championships records#Boys .28U-20.2|CR]]'''\n|{{flagathlete|[[Edwin Baltazar]]|GUA}} || 22.06\n|{{flagathlete|[[Alonso Edward]]|PAN}} || 22.07\n|-\n|[[400 metres]]\n|{{flagathlete|[[Edwin Baltazar]]|GUA}} || 49.75\n|{{flagathlete|[[Gary Robinson (athlete)|Gary Robinson]]|CRC}} || 49.89\n|{{flagathlete|[[Guillermo Berm\u00fadez]]|GUA}} || 51.45\n|-\n|[[800 metres]]\n|{{flagathlete|[[Aurelio S\u00e1nchez]]|NCA}} || 1:56.33\n|{{flagathlete|[[Carlos \u00c1lvarez (athlete)|Carlos \u00c1lvarez]]|GUA}} || 1:57.65\n|{{flagathlete|[[Lino P\u00e9rez]]|PAN}} || 1:57.92\n|-\n|[[1500 metres]]\n|{{flagathlete|[[Carlos